<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - POWER TAKE OFF: ROCKWELL REAR ENGINE MOUNTED - CLEAN AND
        INSPECT
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>CLEAN AND INSPECT</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="0">
            <title>REPAIRING OR REPLACING THE PARTS</title>
            <para>Replace worn or damaged parts. The following are some examples to check.</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Replace any fastener if the corners of the head are worn.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Replace the washers if damaged.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Replace gaskets and oil seals.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Clean the parts and apply new gasket material where required when the unit is
                    assembled.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove nicks, mars and burrs from parts having machined or ground surfaces. Use a fine
                    file, india stone or crocus cloth for this purpose.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Clean and repair the threads of fasteners and holes. Use a die or tap of the correct
                    size or a fine file for this purpose.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Threads must be clean and undamaged so that accurate adjustments and correct torque values can
                        be applied to fasteners and parts.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <para>Tighten all fasteners to the correct torque values. Refer to the
                <hotlnk document="s13003_13.xml" xrefid="hl1300302">TORQUE CHART
                    <xref refid="hl1300302"/>
                </hotlnk>
            </para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
